snippet.textDisplay:
I really dislike people who act so shocked or angry at how crazy or silly these movies go with their set pieces and action. Like, come on?! The Fast and Furious movies have been over-the-top since like 4-5. Heck, even the first 3 were cheezy, silly action movies... Just with slightly less crazy. These movies are blockbuster action movies, they are not made to be realistic or accurate or even down to earth... They are made to be wacky and crazy. They are made to be enjoyed and just have a good time with... No deep plot, no heavy thinking... Just sit back and enjoy the mayhem that appears on screen with a cast of loveable and silly characters. I think some people take movies too seriously sometimes... They forget the first reason movies exist, 'to entertain'.

If this kind of movie isn't someone's thing, that's fine. But to the people to criticize or complain about all the stuff that happens like they expected Citizen Kane, then just stop...Please.

snippet.textDisplay: I guess Joe didn't see Fate of the Furious. Charlize Theron isn't a new villain, she was the villain of the last movie, and Cipher is her code name. She controlled Dom and made him turn (kinda) against his "family." Come on, she was the one who shot Dom's ex love, execution style, right in front of him. I biggest problem I have with this movie is, Dom suddenly has a brother. A movie series that hammers and hammers in on the whole "family" crap, never mentioned a brother? Dom even goes into detail about his young past where his father dying on the race track, yet he can't mention a "bad ass assassin" brother? Weak, lol. What would have been better would have been him being Paul Walker's brother or something. We never got any Paul Walker background, so having John Cena come in as Paul's brother, they could have spun a decent story, and that would make more sense why Paul's wife came back after "retiring" and having a family and all, lol. It's going to be funny when all these bad guys just show up in the next movie all as friends. I swear, The Fast and Furious franchise is just a live action, car version of Dragon Ball Z, lol.

snippet.textDisplay: Disagree on the Supra Joe. On paper it looks tame. I actually drove one hard (thanks to a friend who works at a dealer who borrowed one for the weekend) and it IS GOOD.  Accelerates like and MF and when you stomp on the brakes, the negative G's will press you against the seatbelt. It makes more than the 335 advertised. Its more like the 380bhp that the BMW Z4 comes with but even that is a little low. Toyota just under-rates it on paper just to satisfy BMW. From Car and Driver: "We found that the Supra puts down 339 horsepower and 427 lb-ft of torque at the wheels, which helps to explain its impressive accelerative ability." I mean come on man, it does 0-60 in 3.8 seconds for less than 60 grand. Not even the Mustang GT or Camaro SS are that quick. Only the C8 Corvette does better by price and I guarantee Chevy is MSRP'ing those at a loss for the hype like Nissan did with the GT-R when it first came out (69k (nice)) in 2008. Now you can't buy a new GT-R for less than 100k despite the car only receiving minor incremental updates since then..
